# Video Playback Development

## Overview
Guidelines for developing video playback components in the Telecine system, focusing on the EFPlayer component and related video processing infrastructure.

## Key Components

### EFPlayer Component (`services/web/app/components/EFPlayer.tsx`)
- React component wrapping @editframe/react Preview, Scrubber, TimeDisplay, TogglePlay
- Supports both code injection and React children for content
- Uses web components with slot-based architecture for controls
- Styled with Tailwind CSS for consistent UI

### Video Processing Pipeline
- **C++ Transcode Library** (`lib/transcode/`): FFmpeg integration for video processing
- **Segment Encoder** (`lib/render/SegmentEncoder.server.ts`): Server-side video encoding
- **ISOBMFF Processing** (`services/worker-process-isobmff/`): ISO Base Media File Format handling

## Development Patterns

### Component Structure
```tsx
// Use @editframe/react components for video functionality
import { Preview, Scrubber, TimeDisplay, TogglePlay } from "@editframe/react";

// Wrap in container with proper styling
<div className="relative w-full">
  <Preview className="bg-slate-800 w-full h-full" ref={previewRef}>
    {/* Content goes here */}
  </Preview>
</div>
```

### Control Integration
- Use slot-based architecture for custom controls
- Integrate with Heroicons for consistent iconography
- Apply hover states and accessibility considerations

### Video Format Support
- Focus on seekable formats (requirement for random access)
- Support just-in-time transcoding for unsupported formats
- Leverage FFmpeg 6.1 capabilities through C++ addon

## Implementation Guidelines

### Performance Considerations
- Use refs for direct DOM manipulation when needed
- Implement progressive enhancement (server-first, client-enhanced)
- Consider memory management for video buffers

### Error Handling
- Graceful degradation for unsupported formats
- Network error recovery for streaming content
- User feedback for processing states

### Testing
- Unit tests for component logic
- Integration tests for video processing pipeline
- Browser tests for actual playback functionality

## Related Files
- `lib/transcode/src/playback.cpp` - Core C++ playback logic
- `lib/render/Video2EncodingController.server.ts` - Server-side encoding control
- `services/web/app/api/v1/isobmff_files/` - Video file API endpoints

## FFmpeg Integration
- Custom C++ Node.js addon for performance
- Support for seeking to arbitrary timestamps
- Real-time transcoding capabilities
- Format validation and metadata extraction
